cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with analyzing Twitter microblogs and their semantic relations between concepts. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper may involve developing software for data mining and analysis. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper involves analyzing and extracting information from large amounts of data. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is relevant as the paper involves analyzing natural language text in the form of tweets. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as the paper discusses the societal implications of analyzing tweet data for event forecasting.
